H0.text: A sophomore is a student in which year of a US college. Fresh

H1.text: A sophomore is a student in which year of a US college. Junior

H2.text: A sophomore is a student in which year of a US college. Senior

H3.text: A sophomore is a student in which year of a US college. Secs

A4.text: The term sophomore is also used to refer to a student in the second year of college or university studies in the United States; typically a college sophomore is 19 to 20 years old.

A5.text: Junior (education year), the third year of high school or college in the United States

A6.text: Senior (education), a student in the final year of high school, college or university.
